There is a font rendering bug appearing on **ALL** versions on libgdx past 1.7.1.

In 1.71 I have:
![selection_027](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/2534771/25548569/5a9d0698-2c6d-11e7-9a42-2fcf3262576a.png)

While in 1.7.2 and tried also 1.9.6
![selection_026](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/2534771/25548567/52a416de-2c6d-11e7-903a-0dbf84699c28.png)

```java
private static float scale = ScreenResolution.GAMEHEIGHT / Gdx.graphics.getHeight();
private static void createFont(Font font, Skin skin) {
   generator = new FreeTypeFontGenerator(Gdx.files.internal("data/fonts/" + font.getTtfName()));
   FreeTypeFontGenerator.FreeTypeFontParameter parameter = new FreeTypeFontGenerator.FreeTypeFontParameter();

   parameter.minFilter = Texture.TextureFilter.Linear;
   parameter.magFilter = Texture.TextureFilter.Linear;
   parameter.genMipMaps = false;
   parameter.size = (int) Math.ceil(font.getSize() / scale);

   BitmapFont generatedFont = generator.generateFont(parameter);

   generatedFont.getData().setScale((int) 1f * scale);

   fontsList.add(generatedFont);
   skin.add(font.getName(), generatedFont, BitmapFont.class);
}
```

#### Version of LibGDX and/or relevant dependencies
1.7.2 to most recent 1.9.6

